  "response_text": "Here is a comprehensive, science-backed meal plan designed to support **sustainable weight loss** (approximately 1–2 lbs per week). It focuses on **high volume, high protein, and high fiber** to keep you full while in a calorie deficit.\n\n**Important Note:** Calorie needs vary. This plan is based on a **~1,500–1,700 calorie** target (suitable for many women or smaller men). Adjust portion sizes (e.g., rice, oil, nuts) up or down based on your specific needs and activity level. Always consult a doctor before starting a new diet.\n\n---\n\n### The Core Principles of This Plan\n- **Protein at every meal:** 20–30g per meal (chicken, fish, tofu, eggs, Greek yogurt).\n- **Fiber-rich veggies:** Fill half your plate with non-starchy vegetables (broccoli, spinach, peppers, cauliflower).\n- **Healthy fats:** In moderation (avocado, olive oil, nuts, seeds).\n- **Complex carbs:** Prioritize whole grains (quinoa, oats, sweet potatoes) and legumes.\n- **Hydration:** Drink 2–3 liters of water daily. Drink a glass before meals to reduce appetite.\n- **No liquid calories:** Avoid soda, juice, and sugary coffee drinks.\n\n---\n\n### 7-Day Sample Meal Plan\n\n#### **Day 1**\n- **Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs (2 eggs + 1 cup spinach) with 1 slice whole-wheat toast and ½ avocado.\n- **Lunch:** Large grilled chicken salad (4 oz chicken, mixed greens, cucumber, tomato, bell pepper, 2 tbsp vinaigrette).\n- **Snack:** 1 apple + 1 tbsp almond butter.\n- **Dinner:** Baked salmon (5 oz) with roasted broccoli and ½ cup quinoa.\n- **Total ~1,550 calories**\n\n#### **Day 2**\n- **Breakfast:** Greek yogurt (¾ cup plain, 2% fat) with ½ cup berries and 1 tbsp chia seeds.\n- **Lunch:** Turkey and veggie wrap (whole-wheat tortilla, 4 oz turkey, lettuce, tomato, mustard, ¼ avocado).\n- **Snack:** 1 hard-boiled egg + 1 small carrot.\n- **Dinner:** Stir-fry (5 oz shrimp, 2 cups mixed veggies [bok choy, bell pepper, snap peas], 1 tsp sesame oil, served over ½ cup brown rice).\n- **Total ~1,600 calories**\n\n#### **Day 3**\n- **Breakfast:** Oatmeal (½ cup rolled oats, 1 cup water) topped with 1 scoop protein powder (vanilla) and ½ cup blueberries.\n- **Lunch:** Lentil soup (1.5 cups) with a side salad (2 cups greens, 1 tbsp dressing).\n- **Snack:** 1 small pear + 10 almonds.\n- **Dinner:** Grilled chicken breast (5 oz) with roasted asparagus and 1 medium sweet potato (baked).\n- **Total ~1,550 calories**\n\n#### **Day 4**\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie (1 cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 scoop protein powder, 1 cup spinach, ½ banana, 1 tbsp flaxseed).\n- **Lunch:** Tuna salad (1 can tuna in water, 1 tbsp Greek yogurt, celery, onion) over 2 cups mixed greens + 10 whole-wheat crackers.\n- **Snack:** Cottage cheese (½ cup, low-fat) with black pepper and cucumber slices.\n- **Dinner:** Lean beef stir-fry (4 oz sirloin, 2 cups broccoli, bell pepper, ginger, garlic, 1 tsp oil). No rice or noodles.\n- **Total ~1,550 calories**\n\n#### **Day 5**\n- **Breakfast:** 2 eggs (any style) + 1 cup sautéed zucchini and mushrooms + 1 slice turkey bacon.\n- **Lunch:** Quinoa bowl (½ cup cooked quinoa, 4 oz grilled chicken, 1 cup roasted veggies, 2 tbsp hummus).\n- **Snack:** 1 cup edamame (in pods) or ½ cup shelled.\n- **Dinner:** Baked cod (5 oz) with lemon and herbs, served with sautéed spinach and ½ cup brown rice.\n- **Total ~1,600 calories**\n\n#### **Day 6**\n- **Breakfast:** Protein pancakes (2 eggs + 1 mashed banana + 1 scoop protein powder, cooked) topped with ½ cup berries.\n- **Lunch:** Large salad (4 oz grilled tofu or chicken, 2 cups romaine, ½ cup chickpeas, tomato, cucumber, 2 tbsp tahini dressing).\n- **Snack:** 1 small orange + 1 string cheese.\n- **Dinner:** Zucchini noodles (\"zoodles\") with 4 oz lean ground turkey, marinara sauce (no sugar added), and a side of 1 cup steamed green beans.\n- **Total ~1,550 calories**\n\n#### **Day 7** (Flexible \"Refuel\" Day)\n- **Breakfast:** 2 eggs + 1 slice whole-wheat toast + ½ grapefruit.\n- **Lunch:** Leftover dinner from Day 6 or a simple chicken wrap.\n- **Snack:** 1 cup mixed melon or berries.\n- **Dinner:** **Your choice** (pizza, burger, pasta) – but limit to **one serving** and add a large side salad first. This helps prevent binge cravings.\n- **Total ~1,700 calories**\n\n---\n\n### Key Tips for Success\n\n1.  **Pre-portion snacks:** Don't eat from the bag. Count out almonds, crackers, or chips.\n2.  **Don't skip meals:** Skipping often leads to overeating later. Eat every 3–4 hours.\n3.  **Watch the \"healthy\" traps:** Granola, dried fruit, nuts, and avocado are healthy but calorie-dense. Measure them.\n4.  **Sleep & Stress:** Poor sleep and high cortisol (stress) can stall weight loss. Aim for 7–9 hours of sleep.\n5.  **Movement:** Pair this plan with 30 minutes of brisk walking daily and 2–3 strength training sessions per week for best results.\n\n### Sample Grocery List (For the Week)\n\n**Produce:**\n- Spinach, mixed greens, broccoli, bell peppers, zucchini, asparagus, cucumber, tomatoes, lemons, berries, apples, pears, bananas, avocado, garlic, ginger.\n\n**Protein:**\n- Chicken breast, salmon, cod, shrimp, lean ground turkey, eggs, Greek yogurt, cottage cheese, tofu, tuna (canned).\n\n**Pantry:**\n- Rolled oats, quinoa, brown rice, lentils, whole-wheat tortillas, almonds, chia seeds, flaxseed, olive oil, vinaigrette, marinara (no sugar), spices (garlic powder, black pepper, paprika, oregano).\n\n**Dairy/Alternatives:**\n- Unsweetened almond milk, string cheese, butter (small amounts for cooking).\n\n---\n\n**Disclaimer:**",
